1
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:05,693
(Mio) What do you mean you can't arrest me?

2
00:00:05,693 --> 00:00:07,363
(Endo) It has been determined that it was an unexpected accident.

3
00:00:07,363 --> 00:00:09,759
I don't want to see you again for the rest of my life

4
00:00:09,759 --> 00:00:13,033
< Is it okay to undo a mistake? >

5
00:00:13,033 --> 00:00:15,066
(Sakuma) I'm sorry.

6
00:00:15,066 --> 00:00:18,099
(Taro) If my sister does her best, everything will go wrong.

7
00:00:18,099 --> 00:00:20,759
(Chihiro) People die because you do unnecessary things.

8
00:00:20,759 --> 00:00:23,330
This is the second time with Dad, right?

9
00:00:24,660 --> 00:00:28,660
⚟♬「Small sunset glow」

10
00:00:28,660 --> 00:00:42,429
⚟♬〜

11
00:00:42,429 --> 00:00:44,858
(Takeshi) Ah...

12
00:00:47,132 --> 00:00:49,693
(Takeshi) Uh...

13
00:00:49,693 --> 00:01:04,099
⚟♬〜

14
00:01:04,099 --> 00:01:08,891
(Chihiro) I wish it was all a dream...

15
00:01:11,363 --> 00:01:14,264
that you were born

16
00:01:14,264 --> 00:01:19,858
♬〜

17
00:01:19,858 --> 00:01:21,528
(Yume) Who?

18
00:01:21,528 --> 00:01:28,396
♬〜

19
00:01:28,396 --> 00:01:31,198
Mio-chan...

20
00:01:31,198 --> 00:01:38,891
(breathing heavily)

21
00:01:41,231 --> 00:01:46,693
(breathing heavily)

22
00:01:48,264 --> 00:01:52,264
(Chihiro) So you quit your job? Huh?

23
00:01:52,264 --> 00:01:55,792
what? Just do it... What's the key? Taro's key

24
00:01:55,792 --> 00:01:57,627
You haven't taken a bath, have you?

25
00:01:57,627 --> 00:02:00,000
It smells like rotten onions.

26
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:02,429
Go home

27
00:02:02,429 --> 00:02:05,957
I met Mio Osako

28
00:02:05,957 --> 00:02:07,627
Huh?

29
00:02:15,462 --> 00:02:18,792
(Chihiro)《Sorry for the inconvenience, this is Yume Nakata's mother》

30
00:02:18,792 --> 00:02:21,231
《Is it okay now? 》

31
00:02:22,759 --> 00:02:27,099
(Chihiro)《I know it's rude to suddenly barge in, but...》

32
00:02:36,429 --> 00:02:38,264
``I'll pay you so please pretend it never happened''

33
00:02:38,264 --> 00:02:39,924
Does that mean? 》

34
00:02:42,099 --> 00:02:47,363
``Are you thinking about going to court? 》

35
00:02:47,363 --> 00:02:49,363
``Why are you doing this? 》

36
00:02:49,363 --> 00:02:51,891
《What? 》 《For my daughter who is over 20 years old

37
00:02:51,891 --> 00:02:56,594
There is also a thing like that, but I would call it a toxic parent...》

38
00:02:56,594 --> 00:02:59,231
《I heard that you were ignored for a long time》

39
00:03:02,330 --> 00:03:05,957
(Chihiro)《One thing I can say is...》

40
00:03:05,957 --> 00:03:08,132
“My life was ruined by that kid.

41
00:03:08,132 --> 00:03:11,495
You're not the first.

42
00:03:11,495 --> 00:03:13,165
《What? 》

43
00:03:14,198 --> 00:03:19,264
《I heard you were friends》

44
00:03:19,264 --> 00:03:22,330
《Please pick it up》

45
00:03:22,330 --> 00:03:26,693
``You won't believe me if I say it's for you, right?'' 》

46
00:03:26,693 --> 00:03:29,693
《What? 》《If it goes to court

47
00:03:29,693 --> 00:03:33,066
Even if you don't like it, you remember that child.

48
00:03:33,066 --> 00:03:35,231
《What that child did

49
00:03:35,231 --> 00:03:43,000
The time we spent together while pretending to be fine, the lies I told you...

50
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:45,660
``I think it's natural to be angry.''

51
00:03:45,660 --> 00:03:50,297
``But if you make a mistake then

52
00:03:50,297 --> 00:03:54,726
If by some chance you are accused of a crime,

53
00:03:54,726 --> 00:03:57,660
That's just stupid...》

54
00:04:01,627 --> 00:04:06,099
(Chihiro)《So that you don't suffer any more

55
00:04:06,099 --> 00:04:11,825
Could you please pretend that this time never happened? 》

56
00:04:11,825 --> 00:04:22,396
♬〜

57
00:04:22,396 --> 00:04:24,891
(Chihiro)...I said that, but as expected.

58
00:04:24,891 --> 00:04:29,627
Instead of saying, “Yes, I see.” I just want to think about it.

59
00:04:32,363 --> 00:04:34,033
Where are you going? a little bit!

60
00:04:34,033 --> 00:04:36,231
It's not for Mio-chan, it's for yourself, right?

61
00:04:36,231 --> 00:04:38,363
They say it's bad for society if there's a commotion after a trial...

62
00:04:38,363 --> 00:04:41,627
The condition is that you never show your face again.

63
00:04:41,627 --> 00:04:43,297
Huh?

64
00:04:43,297 --> 00:04:47,000
(Chihiro) The absolute conditions for the settlement that that person came up with.

65
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:49,858
Mom came to tell me that today.

66
00:04:49,858 --> 00:04:53,891
That's why I activated Yume-chan's school performance and said, "I'm sorry, Mio-chan."

67
00:04:53,891 --> 00:04:56,495
If you're planning on going to apologize, you'll be in trouble.

68
00:04:56,495 --> 00:04:59,858
It's not my mother, it's that person.

69
00:05:04,726 --> 00:05:08,528
Don't you like your mother's money?

70
00:05:08,528 --> 00:05:12,132
I want to make amends myself

71
00:05:12,132 --> 00:05:15,231
(Chihiro) Even though I was trying to steal it the other day...

72
00:05:16,825 --> 00:05:20,924
I can't make up for it no matter what I do to you

73
00:05:27,165 --> 00:05:29,132
(Speaker) “The ancients said.”

74
00:05:29,132 --> 00:05:31,594
"An eye for an eye, a tooth for a tooth"

75
00:05:31,594 --> 00:05:33,858
"But I think so."

76
00:05:33,858 --> 00:05:37,165
``You can only find peace of mind by letting go of anger.''

77
00:05:37,165 --> 00:05:40,462
Maybe it can be brought back? ”

78
00:05:40,462 --> 00:05:44,330
"Most of the time, unreasonable bosses don't get promoted."

79
00:05:44,330 --> 00:05:59,660
♬〜

80
00:06:06,363 --> 00:06:10,462
I'm sorry, I could have called you suddenly.

81
00:06:10,462 --> 00:06:17,759
♬〜

82
00:06:17,759 --> 00:06:21,330
It was bad in many ways

83
00:06:25,429 --> 00:06:29,066
I'm thinking of having a funeral.

84
00:06:31,528 --> 00:06:36,165
(Shigehiko) Huh? You haven't been able to do it for a long time, have you?

85
00:06:36,165 --> 00:06:41,396
Well, I guess it's not that big of a deal, but maybe it's just the two of us here.

86
00:06:41,396 --> 00:06:43,561
I mean, I mean...

87
00:06:45,825 --> 00:06:50,627
I want to see my mother off properly.

88
00:06:50,627 --> 00:06:53,924
(Shigehiko) Is it okay? That's really it

89
00:06:53,924 --> 00:06:57,198
No, I don't mind having a funeral at all...

90
00:06:57,198 --> 00:07:00,429
I've already decided that

91
00:07:04,132 --> 00:07:08,462
It's not too much. If things kept going like this, they'd even pretend to be friends, right?

92
00:07:08,462 --> 00:07:11,957
Because the police can't catch me...I thought so too.

93
00:07:11,957 --> 00:07:16,363
I don't think I'll kill you, but I didn't say that...

94
00:07:16,363 --> 00:07:18,033
Mr. Kondo asked me, ``Would you like to go to trial with me?''

95
00:07:18,033 --> 00:07:20,627
If there was a story like that...

96
00:07:20,627 --> 00:07:23,924
But I don't even want to think about it anymore.

97
00:07:23,924 --> 00:07:28,264
That child pushed her mother down and ran away.

98
00:07:28,264 --> 00:07:32,495
That girl and I were friends...

99
00:07:32,495 --> 00:07:36,561
I want to pretend it all never happened anymore

100
00:07:36,561 --> 00:07:38,231
(Sae) Osako-san too

101
00:07:38,231 --> 00:07:40,561
I don't think I'll be satisfied with this as it is.

102
00:07:40,561 --> 00:07:43,792
I'm sure they will fight together in court.

103
00:07:43,792 --> 00:07:47,099
So, if we receive an official reply from Mr. Osako.

104
00:07:47,099 --> 00:07:51,000
Please contact me again.Thank you very much.

105
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:54,330
Well, that's all for today.

106
00:08:05,792 --> 00:08:08,825
(Sakura) My nose hair is really growing.

107
00:08:08,825 --> 00:08:10,495
Huh?

108
00:08:14,396 --> 00:08:17,693
Yes, please do yourself a favor and thank you.

109
00:08:18,792 --> 00:08:24,099
Ah... well, but it's proof that you're alive.

110
00:08:26,957 --> 00:08:29,000
Ah thank you

111
00:08:30,429 --> 00:08:34,033
What happened to that boy recently?

112
00:08:34,033 --> 00:08:36,330
Look, she's absentminded but seems like she's good-natured.

113
00:08:36,330 --> 00:08:41,297
Dad, what do you want to do most when you get out of the hospital? Huh?

114
00:08:41,297 --> 00:08:44,627
Hmm, well...beer, I guess.

115
00:08:44,627 --> 00:08:47,099
Old Man's Desire Shobo

116
00:08:48,231 --> 00:08:50,627
(knock) (Sakura) Hello.

117
00:08:54,330 --> 00:08:56,000
(Sakura) Huh?

118
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:59,396
(Sae) Ah, that's right, I'll buy you something sweet...

119
00:09:05,396 --> 00:09:09,330
I'm really sorry

120
00:09:12,660 --> 00:09:15,165
I was absent from work without permission...

121
00:09:15,165 --> 00:09:18,792
There have been many mistakes so far...

122
00:09:18,792 --> 00:09:24,462
I'm really sorry for the inconvenience.

123
00:09:24,462 --> 00:09:34,759
♬〜

124
00:09:34,759 --> 00:09:36,726
please

125
00:09:40,429 --> 00:09:44,363
I need money, just one more chance...

126
00:09:44,363 --> 00:09:46,297
(Yonemoto) In this world

127
00:09:46,297 --> 00:09:50,495
There are irreparable mistakes

128
00:09:52,495 --> 00:09:57,297
Sorry, it's our company policy.

129
00:09:57,297 --> 00:10:15,000
♬〜

130
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:20,561
"Don't just call yourself the worst."

131
00:10:34,462 --> 00:10:36,660
(Priest) Do you need anything?

132
00:10:36,660 --> 00:10:39,363
Ah... uh...

133
00:10:39,363 --> 00:10:44,000
I saw the words on the table and...

134
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:48,000
(Chief Priest) I am currently in meditation, so please come again.

135
00:10:49,165 --> 00:10:51,759
(Sound of tapping) Go!

136
00:10:53,396 --> 00:10:55,825
Sorry...

137
00:10:59,495 --> 00:11:01,165
Ah...

138
00:11:03,132 --> 00:11:08,825
Fired from work...

139
00:11:08,825 --> 00:11:10,693
No, I mean fired...

140
00:11:10,693 --> 00:11:14,132
After all, it's disgusting to see these two talking together.

141
00:11:14,132 --> 00:11:16,429
(sound of breathing)

142
00:11:21,066 --> 00:11:24,363
Was it effective? Huh?

143
00:11:31,495 --> 00:11:35,033
I went there with Mr. Osako the other day...

144
00:11:35,033 --> 00:11:37,198
Huh?

145
00:11:37,198 --> 00:11:39,891
I thought I should apologize properly.

146
00:11:39,891 --> 00:11:43,165
"I'm sorry"

147
00:11:43,165 --> 00:11:48,957
From the other side's perspective, it's just violence.

148
00:11:48,957 --> 00:11:55,891
And... I actually... Huh?

149
00:11:59,627 --> 00:12:05,495
I'm glad I didn't get caught...

150
00:12:05,495 --> 00:12:11,396
I still think that way, actually.

151
00:12:13,297 --> 00:12:16,957
I feel like I have to forgive myself

152
00:12:16,957 --> 00:12:18,957
I hear it often...

153
00:12:21,066 --> 00:12:24,528
But that's probably

154
00:12:24,528 --> 00:12:28,033
I think this is a story about someone who has achieved some level of success.

155
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:41,462
Mio-chan, how was it?

156
00:12:45,726 --> 00:12:48,330
So many things...

157
00:13:10,165 --> 00:13:12,858
Thank you for your hard work.This will be my next order.

158
00:13:12,858 --> 00:13:15,594
Thank you very much (employee) Yes, thank you very much.

159
00:13:16,594 --> 00:13:21,231
Yes, I will make arrangements as soon as possible.Yes, please excuse me.

160
00:13:24,231 --> 00:13:26,363
Mr. Umada, could you please sign this?

161
00:13:26,363 --> 00:13:28,462
(Umada) That's it, Osako-chan.

162
00:13:28,462 --> 00:13:30,891
Materials for next week's meeting with Sushimaru-san

163
00:13:30,891 --> 00:13:32,924
Would you mind making it for Pepe instead?

164
00:13:32,924 --> 00:13:34,825
Okay, I'll do it (Umada), please.

165
00:13:34,825 --> 00:13:36,495
yes

166
00:13:40,792 --> 00:13:43,132
Ah, what?

167
00:13:43,132 --> 00:13:45,891
This is delicious corn tea

168
00:13:45,891 --> 00:13:48,726
That one in the hot water room, Shiono-kun, is that the one you brought?

169
00:13:48,726 --> 00:13:53,594
Ah... I got it when I went to sales, but I'm not good at it.

170
00:13:53,594 --> 00:13:55,495
I can take it home if you like? There's more

171
00:13:55,495 --> 00:14:00,000
Huh? Is that okay? I'm happy thank you

172
00:14:01,429 --> 00:14:04,858
Ah, does it feel like a grassland in Hokkaido?

173
00:14:04,858 --> 00:14:06,528
(Shiono) No, it seems to be Miyazaki sorghum.

174
00:14:06,528 --> 00:14:08,693
What, what's wrong? Huh?

175
00:14:08,693 --> 00:14:10,363
(Shiono) Why does it have such a fairy-tale feel?

176
00:14:10,363 --> 00:14:12,033
Is it happening? Huh?

177
00:14:12,033 --> 00:14:15,165
What about the guts? Is that enough? Gut?

178
00:14:15,165 --> 00:14:17,396
The other day I said, ``It's boiling over.''

179
00:14:17,396 --> 00:14:19,561
Because his face looked like Hannya.

180
00:14:19,561 --> 00:14:22,132
Something like this...

181
00:14:22,132 --> 00:14:24,561
(Umada) Osako-chan, I'm sorry but...

182
00:14:24,561 --> 00:14:27,000
It's tea. I'll bring it right away.

183
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:30,594
(Umada) Whoa, it's been a while since you last appeared?

184
00:14:30,594 --> 00:14:32,825
Osako Smile Kyuu

185
00:14:32,825 --> 00:14:35,825
Huh? Huh? Squeak...

186
00:14:35,825 --> 00:14:40,330
♬(humming)

187
00:14:42,825 --> 00:14:45,693
(Sae) Hehe, excuse me.

188
00:14:46,693 --> 00:14:48,462
(Sae) Hello.

189
00:14:48,462 --> 00:14:52,396
If this is okay... (Sae) Ah, sorry, always.

190
00:14:52,396 --> 00:14:56,693
Were you about to be discharged from the hospital? (Sae) Yes, finally next week

191
00:14:58,594 --> 00:15:02,165
that…

192
00:15:02,165 --> 00:15:03,891
(Sae) Hehe?

193
00:15:03,891 --> 00:15:06,858
(Sae) I always thought the coffee here was bad.

194
00:15:06,858 --> 00:15:11,462
I was drinking, but when I thought I had finished drinking it...

195
00:15:11,462 --> 00:15:13,660
Hehehe

196
00:15:13,660 --> 00:15:17,066
Sorry, I haven't been able to answer the phone for a while.

197
00:15:17,066 --> 00:15:19,693
Ah, no, I'm sorry too, so many times.

198
00:15:19,693 --> 00:15:23,264
Oh no, you came to Mr. Osako too, right?

199
00:15:23,264 --> 00:15:27,594
That person's mother Chihiro Nakata ah yeah...

200
00:15:27,594 --> 00:15:31,528
You're already kidding, right? I'll pay for it, so don't go to court.

201
00:15:31,528 --> 00:15:34,231
Don't tell anyone, just pretend you didn't say it

202
00:15:34,231 --> 00:15:37,561
If a child is a child, a parent is also a parent.

203
00:15:37,561 --> 00:15:40,693
Um... (Sae) It's about the trial.

204
00:15:40,693 --> 00:15:43,132
I talked to a lawyer about Mr. Osako.

205
00:15:43,132 --> 00:15:45,759
Let's have a meeting next time.

206
00:15:45,759 --> 00:15:48,033
After all, it's topical.

207
00:15:48,033 --> 00:15:50,363
If Mr. Osako and I filed a lawsuit together,

208
00:15:50,363 --> 00:15:52,891
The media, well, it's a vulgar way to say it, but

209
00:15:52,891 --> 00:15:54,561
I think the bite is good.

210
00:15:54,561 --> 00:15:56,924
that! (Sae) Yes?

211
00:15:58,000 --> 00:16:03,594
I don't judge

212
00:16:03,594 --> 00:16:07,066
Huh? Sorry

213
00:16:07,066 --> 00:16:14,693
But I still want it all to be over...

214
00:16:14,693 --> 00:16:16,429
Ah... Huh?

215
00:16:16,429 --> 00:16:21,099
Today I wanted to tell you exactly that.

216
00:16:24,330 --> 00:16:29,759
I'm thinking of holding my mother's funeral next weekend.

217
00:16:29,759 --> 00:16:36,363
So... I saw her off properly there...

218
00:16:36,363 --> 00:16:39,924
Does that mean you accept that mother's settlement?

219
00:16:41,627 --> 00:16:45,297
I'm thinking of doing that

220
00:16:45,297 --> 00:16:47,627
Of course, when Mr. Kondo is on trial,

221
00:16:47,627 --> 00:16:50,462
If there's anything I can do, it's absolutely...

222
00:16:50,462 --> 00:16:54,660
But I want it to end

223
00:16:54,660 --> 00:16:57,660
Was it because we were friends?

224
00:16:57,660 --> 00:17:00,198
It really... doesn't matter at all.

225
00:17:00,198 --> 00:17:04,594
(Sae) Then why?

226
00:17:04,594 --> 00:17:07,660
I'm really sorry

227
00:17:10,495 --> 00:17:14,462
Um... excuse me.

228
00:17:14,462 --> 00:17:17,363
(Sae) Then, can I say something?

229
00:17:17,363 --> 00:17:19,033
Huh?

230
00:17:19,033 --> 00:17:25,693
I still don't believe your mother was innocent.

231
00:17:27,528 --> 00:17:31,957
your mother wrote a will

232
00:17:31,957 --> 00:17:37,759
If I hadn't climbed up to that rooftop of my own free will.

233
00:17:37,759 --> 00:17:44,429
That person didn't even go up to the roof to help.

234
00:17:44,429 --> 00:17:49,594
Isn't that why the police can't arrest you?

235
00:17:49,594 --> 00:17:57,792
Is it because you are afraid to decide who is the worst?

236
00:17:57,792 --> 00:18:01,528
Huh... (Sae) Does that mean there won't be a trial?

237
00:18:01,528 --> 00:18:06,132
Does that mean you honestly think so too?

238
00:18:07,363 --> 00:18:14,330
The worst person isn't the last person who pushed me...

239
00:18:14,330 --> 00:18:16,330
Ha...

240
00:18:16,330 --> 00:18:21,462
♬〜

241
00:18:21,462 --> 00:18:23,825
Sorry, excuse me

242
00:18:23,825 --> 00:18:31,891
♬〜

243
00:18:38,297 --> 00:18:40,363
(Endo) Um, sorry.

244
00:18:42,165 --> 00:18:44,891
(Endo) Ah... Hello.

245
00:18:44,891 --> 00:18:48,264
Ah... I'm sorry.

246
00:18:48,264 --> 00:18:50,165
(Endo) Ah, no... please go first.

247
00:18:50,165 --> 00:18:56,033
Oh no...my bus is different.

248
00:18:56,033 --> 00:18:57,693
(Endo) Huh?

249
00:18:57,693 --> 00:19:01,528
Until I realized that my bus wasn't this one.

250
00:19:01,528 --> 00:19:06,825
I remember... so here you go.

251
00:19:12,528 --> 00:19:17,132
Do you like cunt? Huh?

252
00:19:17,132 --> 00:19:19,660
I lost at pachinko

253
00:19:19,660 --> 00:19:23,594
Maybe I was confused, or maybe I was wrong.

254
00:19:23,594 --> 00:19:26,000
I bought 5 of them out of desperation.

255
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:27,660
Huh?

256
00:19:31,429 --> 00:19:34,924
(Endo) Have you calmed down a little?

257
00:19:34,924 --> 00:19:40,066
That's what I thought... Huh?

258
00:19:40,066 --> 00:19:44,660
Well, I guess I'll have a funeral anyway.

259
00:19:44,660 --> 00:19:48,627
I haven't been able to do it for a long time, so next weekend

260
00:19:48,627 --> 00:19:50,297
is that so

261
00:19:55,066 --> 00:19:57,594
Do you play pachinko?

262
00:19:57,594 --> 00:20:01,660
Huh? Huh, ah... I'm off duty today.

263
00:20:01,660 --> 00:20:06,330
No, I'm not blaming you there.

264
00:20:06,330 --> 00:20:11,363
I got addicted to it when I was a student and stopped playing it.

265
00:20:11,363 --> 00:20:15,528
Since my wife passed away,

266
00:20:15,528 --> 00:20:17,627
If my daughter finds out, she will get angry.

267
00:20:17,627 --> 00:20:19,462
Huh? Huh?

268
00:20:19,462 --> 00:20:23,330
Ah... no, I'm sorry, I thought you were alone.

269
00:20:23,330 --> 00:20:28,000
I became independent last year, so I'm alone now.

270
00:20:37,891 --> 00:20:42,132
Will it be the same after 10 years?

271
00:20:42,132 --> 00:20:44,825
(Endo) What do you mean by "same"?

272
00:20:48,132 --> 00:20:50,462
This feeling

273
00:20:56,132 --> 00:20:59,165
I think things have changed a little.

274
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:07,231
(Endo) At that time, I tried not to think about things.

275
00:21:07,231 --> 00:21:12,528
But in the end, I thought about it and got confused, and my daughter...

276
00:21:15,594 --> 00:21:19,198
(Endo) My daughter wanted to talk about her mother.

277
00:21:19,198 --> 00:21:25,066
But I don't want to do this, so I run away to work or play pachinko...

278
00:21:25,066 --> 00:21:31,495
At that time, I wish we had spent more time together.

279
00:21:31,495 --> 00:21:34,693
I knew it because of my job.

280
00:21:34,693 --> 00:21:37,891
Even before my wife died...

281
00:21:39,594 --> 00:21:44,132
About people who die in the same way

282
00:21:45,693 --> 00:21:49,198
(Endo) At that time, I was honestly talking about people like that...

283
00:21:49,198 --> 00:21:55,231
♬〜

284
00:21:55,231 --> 00:22:03,264
I don't want to think that my wife is the same as those people.

285
00:22:05,792 --> 00:22:08,033
(Endo) Sorry, that's a strange thing to say.

286
00:22:08,033 --> 00:22:15,495
♬〜

287
00:22:38,099 --> 00:22:40,495
Everyone has no place to stay

288
00:22:42,198 --> 00:22:43,858
(cell phone vibration sound)

289
00:22:48,165 --> 00:23:08,231
♬〜

290
00:23:08,231 --> 00:23:20,264
♬〜

291
00:23:20,264 --> 00:23:21,924
(Sae)《Do you really think so?

292
00:23:21,924 --> 00:23:25,099
Does that mean you think so? 》

293
00:23:25,099 --> 00:23:28,132
《The worst thing is

294
00:23:28,132 --> 00:23:33,429
Not that person who pushed me in the end...

295
00:23:36,495 --> 00:23:38,858
(chime)

296
00:23:38,858 --> 00:23:44,000
♬〜

297
00:24:03,000 --> 00:24:06,066
(bell)

298
00:24:09,264 --> 00:24:13,330
Please (Chihiro) Yes.

299
00:24:13,330 --> 00:24:16,858
Thank you for contacting us.

300
00:24:25,330 --> 00:24:28,660
(Chihiro) Huh? This... yes?

301
00:24:30,363 --> 00:24:33,066
Ah, no...

302
00:24:34,693 --> 00:24:36,957
that…

303
00:24:39,759 --> 00:24:43,132
(Chihiro) Please consult with a lawyer about this.

304
00:24:43,132 --> 00:24:46,528
I have also added the conditions you gave me last time.

305
00:24:46,528 --> 00:24:49,165
I also told Yume herself.

306
00:24:49,165 --> 00:24:51,330
Of course, if you have other concerns...

307
00:24:51,330 --> 00:24:55,957
When the train was delayed... Huh?

308
00:24:55,957 --> 00:24:59,462
When a train is delayed due to a personal injury accident

309
00:24:59,462 --> 00:25:02,858
I'm really pissed off.

310
00:25:02,858 --> 00:25:05,858
Who are you who wants to die so early in the morning?

311
00:25:05,858 --> 00:25:09,198
Don't bother people and die on your own

312
00:25:09,198 --> 00:25:11,495
(Chihiro) Um...

313
00:25:11,495 --> 00:25:18,957
Actually, I thought the same about my mother.

314
00:25:18,957 --> 00:25:22,330
Why do you cause so much trouble to people?

315
00:25:22,330 --> 00:25:25,561
He's dead.

316
00:25:25,561 --> 00:25:31,264
Why... would you commit suicide?

317
00:25:36,825 --> 00:25:44,693
I was the one who couldn't forgive my mother the most.

318
00:25:47,231 --> 00:25:48,957
But... that's...

319
00:25:48,957 --> 00:25:55,066
It's true that Yume was the one who pushed me in the end

320
00:25:55,066 --> 00:26:04,759
But... I signed this and everything was a bad dream.

321
00:26:04,759 --> 00:26:09,495
So let's forget everything

322
00:26:09,495 --> 00:26:13,726
Mom herself...

323
00:26:13,726 --> 00:26:18,528
I went up there thinking I wanted to die...

324
00:26:18,528 --> 00:26:20,198
The dream is...

325
00:26:24,099 --> 00:26:30,231
It's like pretending all that didn't happen.

326
00:26:30,231 --> 00:26:36,891
So I still can't sign this.

327
00:26:36,891 --> 00:26:43,561
♬〜

328
00:26:43,561 --> 00:26:49,528
After all, you want to go to court...is that what you mean?

329
00:26:49,528 --> 00:26:51,825
There will be no trial.

330
00:26:51,825 --> 00:26:54,594
The funeral will be held next weekend, and...

331
00:26:54,594 --> 00:26:57,858
(Chihiro) I understand how you feel.

332
00:26:57,858 --> 00:27:05,099
But I guess you don't have to take it so seriously...

333
00:27:05,099 --> 00:27:07,693
This is also because I feel sorry.

334
00:27:07,693 --> 00:27:09,363
Since this is a suggestion...

335
00:27:09,363 --> 00:27:13,099
After all, it's for yourself, right? Because I have a bad reputation

336
00:27:13,099 --> 00:27:14,759
Not so...

337
00:27:14,759 --> 00:27:17,924
If that's the case, then I'm saying it's okay, so...

338
00:27:17,924 --> 00:27:20,924
Because you don't understand that child's true nature.

339
00:27:22,726 --> 00:27:29,099
what do you mean? Eh...

340
00:27:29,099 --> 00:27:32,198
You said this the other day, right?

341
00:27:32,198 --> 00:27:34,000
That kid ruined my life

342
00:27:34,000 --> 00:27:37,165
It's not like I'm the first...

343
00:27:37,165 --> 00:27:39,231
(Chihiro) This...

344
00:27:39,231 --> 00:27:42,957
Is it really corn tea?

345
00:27:42,957 --> 00:27:47,693
Huh? (Chihiro) Ugh... your face is hot...

346
00:27:47,693 --> 00:27:50,132
Huh?

347
00:27:50,132 --> 00:27:54,825
No... corn tea... I'm allergic...

348
00:27:54,825 --> 00:27:59,297
Eh, wait a minute... Huh!? Are you okay?

349
00:27:59,297 --> 00:28:04,000
(breathing heavily)

350
00:28:08,000 --> 00:28:11,627
(Nurse) Once the IV is finished, you can go home.

351
00:28:16,198 --> 00:28:19,561
I'm really sorry

352
00:28:23,198 --> 00:28:29,396
(Chihiro) Could you please reconsider?

353
00:28:32,066 --> 00:28:34,231
(Chihiro) If you're saying the amount isn't enough...

354
00:28:34,231 --> 00:28:36,891
What happened with Yume?

355
00:28:39,957 --> 00:28:43,627
My life has been messed up...

356
00:28:43,627 --> 00:28:46,132
Do you mean you?

357
00:29:03,033 --> 00:29:07,759
Was it the person who hit you?

358
00:29:07,759 --> 00:29:11,561
Yume and Taro's father

359
00:29:11,561 --> 00:29:17,693
That's why I used to say

360
00:29:17,693 --> 00:29:24,462
``I wish I died in an unexpected accident,'' I thought to myself.

361
00:29:24,462 --> 00:29:30,165
But then one day, he really died.

362
00:29:30,165 --> 00:29:32,462
Heart attack...

363
00:29:36,264 --> 00:29:41,792
Yume first found that person when he collapsed.

364
00:29:41,792 --> 00:29:48,066
The day Taro developed a fever, I took him to the hospital...

365
00:29:49,594 --> 00:29:54,924
When Yume found it...

366
00:29:54,924 --> 00:29:57,924
I was still breathing

367
00:29:57,924 --> 00:29:59,594
Huh?

368
00:30:02,165 --> 00:30:06,165
⚟♬「Small sunset glow」

369
00:30:06,165 --> 00:30:08,198
⚟♬〜

370
00:30:08,198 --> 00:30:09,858
"I'm home"

371
00:30:11,561 --> 00:30:13,957
《Dad? 》

372
00:30:16,660 --> 00:30:20,297
(Takeshi)《Idiot! " "sorry"

373
00:30:20,297 --> 00:30:23,957
"quick! I'll kill you.

374
00:30:23,957 --> 00:30:28,561
(breathing heavily)

375
00:30:28,561 --> 00:30:30,792
"quickly…"

376
00:30:30,792 --> 00:30:50,792
⚟♬〜

377
00:30:50,792 --> 00:30:58,792
⚟♬〜

378
00:31:03,924 --> 00:31:10,066
♬〜

379
00:31:10,066 --> 00:31:14,495
(Chihiro) “This is about Mom and Taro.

380
00:31:14,495 --> 00:31:18,198
You helped me, right? ”

381
00:31:18,198 --> 00:31:20,495
Huh?

382
00:31:20,495 --> 00:31:25,495
The first thing she said to me when she came home

383
00:31:28,891 --> 00:31:33,957
Honestly... I'm scared of that girl.

384
00:31:33,957 --> 00:31:39,396
But I don't want to be afraid of my daughter.

385
00:31:39,396 --> 00:31:43,264
He was actually a terrible person

386
00:31:43,264 --> 00:31:47,165
I don't know if that kid could have survived if he had called an ambulance.

387
00:31:47,165 --> 00:31:53,396
At first I thought this was a good thing, but...

388
00:31:53,396 --> 00:31:57,759
Then Yume started speaking.

389
00:32:00,231 --> 00:32:08,726
"Mom, was I really wrong?"

390
00:32:10,924 --> 00:32:14,495
(Chihiro) Every time that girl starts saying things like that

391
00:32:14,495 --> 00:32:20,528
I'm starting to feel like I'm being blamed...

392
00:32:20,528 --> 00:32:26,330
Because I said I wish I died in an unexpected accident...

393
00:32:28,429 --> 00:32:30,330
I did it for my mom.

394
00:32:30,330 --> 00:32:34,660
But is it really wrong? That's it

395
00:32:34,660 --> 00:32:38,825
I feel like that's what that girl is saying...

396
00:32:42,891 --> 00:32:45,528
Taro is still small

397
00:32:45,528 --> 00:32:49,924
I didn't know what happened though

398
00:32:49,924 --> 00:32:56,330
Listen to me talking to Yume, who has just entered elementary school.

399
00:32:57,660 --> 00:33:05,792
Then she said, ``It's not your sister's fault.''

400
00:33:05,792 --> 00:33:10,033
But Yume wasn't convinced at all...

401
00:33:10,033 --> 00:33:14,924
Look closely at me...

402
00:33:14,924 --> 00:33:17,495
I want to say that it's my fault after all.

403
00:33:17,495 --> 00:33:21,462
I thought it was this kid...

404
00:33:27,132 --> 00:33:31,066
that's why…

405
00:33:31,066 --> 00:33:34,396
I ignored them.

406
00:33:38,627 --> 00:33:42,132
(Chihiro) I made a lot of money with that.

407
00:33:42,132 --> 00:33:49,528
After that, I found a new family and life became much more enjoyable...

408
00:33:52,264 --> 00:33:57,000
(Chihiro) I guess it's similar to studying for entrance exams.

409
00:33:57,000 --> 00:34:04,594
Meaning, reason, emotion...etc.

410
00:34:04,594 --> 00:34:09,231
If you start thinking like that, you've lost.

411
00:34:14,132 --> 00:34:18,693
You may not believe me, but...

412
00:34:18,693 --> 00:34:22,264
It wasn't like this from the beginning.

413
00:34:22,264 --> 00:34:28,198
There were things I couldn't do because I had it when I was young.

414
00:34:28,198 --> 00:34:34,066
I want you to have many dreams that you didn't have yet.

415
00:34:34,066 --> 00:34:36,198
Name it...

416
00:34:38,858 --> 00:34:40,528
Huh?

417
00:34:42,759 --> 00:34:47,000
Who do you think was at fault?

418
00:34:47,000 --> 00:34:50,462
Me or Yume...

419
00:34:50,462 --> 00:34:55,165
Cause and effect? Is it my dead husband?

420
00:34:57,066 --> 00:35:01,627
Who… “No one is at fault”?

421
00:35:06,924 --> 00:35:11,792
Honestly, as you said, it's also for my own protection...

422
00:35:11,792 --> 00:35:14,726
I think that was a rude approach.

423
00:35:14,726 --> 00:35:19,693
But about the settlement

424
00:35:19,693 --> 00:35:23,561
Could you please reconsider?

425
00:35:26,297 --> 00:35:29,000
But I...

426
00:35:29,000 --> 00:35:33,858
Can you really forgive me?

427
00:35:33,858 --> 00:35:36,000
About that child

428
00:35:41,924 --> 00:35:47,792
(Chihiro) Are humans really that beautiful?

429
00:35:51,066 --> 00:36:11,066
♬〜

430
00:36:11,066 --> 00:36:31,066
♬〜

431
00:36:31,066 --> 00:36:49,627
♬〜

432
00:36:49,627 --> 00:36:52,396
``Why did you pretend to be my friend? 》

433
00:36:53,924 --> 00:36:55,627
《It's not pretend》

434
00:36:55,627 --> 00:36:57,297
《Mio-chan! 》

435
00:36:57,297 --> 00:37:17,297
♬〜

436
00:37:17,297 --> 00:37:28,462
♬〜

437
00:37:28,462 --> 00:37:41,594
(cell phone vibration sound)

438
00:37:43,726 --> 00:37:47,099
hello

439
00:37:47,099 --> 00:37:50,363
📱Hello

440
00:37:50,363 --> 00:37:54,528
📱I'm talking about your mother.

441
00:37:54,528 --> 00:37:56,198
Huh?

442
00:37:56,198 --> 00:38:01,396
Corn tea...I didn't know I was allergic to it.

443
00:38:01,396 --> 00:38:07,957
It wasn't a big deal, but I was in the hospital just now.

444
00:38:07,957 --> 00:38:10,264
That's right

445
00:38:10,264 --> 00:38:14,198
📱Sorry, I just wanted to let you know.

446
00:38:17,264 --> 00:38:22,429
I see... thank you

447
00:38:28,792 --> 00:38:32,891
📱Okay then... Oh wait...

448
00:38:32,891 --> 00:38:36,066
I'd like to meet and talk.

449
00:38:36,066 --> 00:38:37,726
Huh?

450
00:38:37,726 --> 00:38:40,000
📱Where are you now?

451
00:38:52,000 --> 00:38:56,825
(footsteps)

452
00:39:22,528 --> 00:39:25,891
Where are you going?

453
00:39:25,891 --> 00:39:30,924
Ah... Yeah well...

454
00:39:30,924 --> 00:39:33,231
That's right

455
00:39:38,396 --> 00:39:42,165
I'm sorry about your mother.

456
00:39:42,165 --> 00:39:45,231
No, not at all

457
00:39:46,297 --> 00:39:50,132
I heard a story about when I was a child.

458
00:39:52,627 --> 00:39:56,693
Huh? about your father

459
00:40:02,627 --> 00:40:04,462
I see...

460
00:40:09,561 --> 00:40:11,957
sorry

461
00:40:15,660 --> 00:40:20,594
I don't think it's your fault...

462
00:40:23,528 --> 00:40:27,099
Huh?

463
00:40:27,099 --> 00:40:29,330
no one is at fault

464
00:40:32,033 --> 00:40:34,528
Also about your mother

465
00:40:38,858 --> 00:40:45,891
So I...

466
00:40:45,891 --> 00:40:48,396
I want to forgive you

467
00:40:54,693 --> 00:41:06,627
♬〜

468
00:41:06,627 --> 00:41:08,462
(Sakura) Are you back?

469
00:41:12,165 --> 00:41:17,561
Sister: It seems like you came out, so (Sakura) did you say you went out?

470
00:41:19,231 --> 00:41:23,891
What is that? Stalker?

471
00:41:26,594 --> 00:41:30,297
Sorry for everything

472
00:41:30,297 --> 00:41:37,594
♬〜

473
00:41:37,594 --> 00:41:42,627
Would you like to eat something?

474
00:41:42,627 --> 00:41:44,297
Huh?

475
00:41:44,297 --> 00:42:02,660
♬〜

476
00:42:02,660 --> 00:42:05,132
♬〜

477
00:42:05,132 --> 00:42:07,132
(slapping sound)

478
00:42:07,132 --> 00:42:18,264
♬〜

479
00:42:18,264 --> 00:42:21,099
(Nurse) Are you ready? yes

480
00:42:21,099 --> 00:42:33,264
♬〜

481
00:42:33,264 --> 00:42:35,825
Does that mean you left home?

482
00:42:38,363 --> 00:42:44,165
Taro... I think I'm about to reach my limit at home.

483
00:42:44,165 --> 00:42:49,066
You can't go back if I'm here, so...

484
00:42:50,165 --> 00:42:52,495
I see.

485
00:42:55,462 --> 00:42:59,693
Ah... Is it okay to stay here?

486
00:42:59,693 --> 00:43:02,957
Home It's the other way around, right?

487
00:43:02,957 --> 00:43:07,858
No, no... In that case, tell me before you go up the stairs.

488
00:43:11,363 --> 00:43:13,660
sorry

489
00:43:16,693 --> 00:43:18,792
Well then...

490
00:43:22,066 --> 00:43:23,726
Hey

491
00:43:29,000 --> 00:43:32,099
Why did you suddenly tell me the truth?

492
00:43:39,000 --> 00:43:44,165
Sorry, I don't really understand either.

493
00:44:12,033 --> 00:44:15,000
Maybe it's impossible after all?

494
00:44:17,330 --> 00:44:20,627
Oh sorry! a little bit…

495
00:44:20,627 --> 00:44:22,330
Eh, eh...wait!

496
00:44:22,330 --> 00:44:24,000
Hey, ah, ah!

497
00:44:24,000 --> 00:44:28,000
(Train running sound)

498
00:44:34,000 --> 00:44:38,000
♬〜
